00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:54,595
Saucisson, Mme Fenuze,

455
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:57,194
is the best and the cheapest meat,

456
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:59,715
as it's the only one with no bone!

457
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,639
That's very true.

458
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:04,439
It'd be odd, finding a bone
in your saucisson.

459
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:06,431
Quite hilarious, even.

460
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,671
100 grams, 3 francs 50.

461
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:13,392
- Uncle, a quick word.
- What, without stopping?

462
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:16,233
- It's a locution.
- What the hell's that?

463
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:19,472
You'll find out
as soon as the good lady has left.

464
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:22,473
Your nephew's polite,
treating me like a beggar!

465
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:26,189
Tell him I'm a customer.
One who pays in good money!

466
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:29,910
And we pay you in saucisson:
A currency that never devalues!

467
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:32,435
- Good day, madam.
- Irénée!

468
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:35,797
Quiet! It's the greatest day
of my life and yours.

469
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:38,793
The five cents you make
on that lady's saucisson

470
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,155
shouldn't inspire respect for her.

471
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,595
- Look at this.
- What is it?

472
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:46,832
If this paper was as heavy
as the gold it's worth,

473
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:49,594
- it would break the scale.
- What is it?

474
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:52,069
A contract.
A contract for my talent.

475
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:54,038
Hand me my glasses.

476
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:56,271
No. I'll read it myself.

477
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:58,749
But within the family circle...

478
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:04,999
A family suddenly enriched
by my talent.

479
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:08,550
Uncle, Casimir, Auntie...

480
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:11,671
- What's going on?
- Who knows!

481
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:13,432
- Have you eaten?
- I have.

482
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:15,955
Sit down.
We'll drink champagne after.

483
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:18,315
Uncle, do you know the movies?

484
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:20,994
Yes. A dark room
in which I get bored.

485
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:21,837
Wrong!

486
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:24,395
I don't get bored on purpose!

487
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:26,869
I even get bored getting bored.

488
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:28,393
But that paper?

489
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,870
Uncle, my god-given gift is movies.

490
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:33,156
- What?
- Yes. An actor.

491
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:35,788
Comedy... tragedy...

492
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:36,956
You like it?

493
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:40,949
It's best I know
so we know where we are.

494
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:45,239
A powerful American company
with a subsidiary in France

495
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:48,551
signed with me this engagement.
Listen.

